{"id":392413,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_40-Year-Old_Virgin","text":"e=\"preserve\">\"The 40-Year-Old Virgin\" is a 2005 American romantic comedy movie. It was written, directed and co-produced by Judd Apatow.\nSteve Carell plays the eponymous virgin who lives alone and is involuntarily celibate. He works in the stockroom of an electronics store and is socially inept. Carell also wrote the script. The movie got mostly good reviews from critics.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"United_States","surface_form":"American","offset":48},{"uri":"Romance_movie","surface_form":"romantic","offset":57},{"uri":"Comedy_movie","surface_form":"comedy movie","offset":66},{"uri":"Screenwriter","surface_form":"written","offset":87},{"uri":"Movie_director","surface_form":"directed","offset":96},{"uri":"Movie_producer","surface_form":"produced","offset":112},{"uri":"Judd_Apatow","surface_form":"Judd Apatow","offset":124},{"uri":"Steve_Carell","surface_form":"Steve Carell","offset":137},{"uri":"Virgin","surface_form":"virgin","offset":170},{"uri":"Involuntarily_celibate","surface_form":"involuntarily celibate","offset":200},{"uri":"Stockroom","surface_form":"stockroom","offset":240},{"uri":"Electronics","surface_form":"electronics","offset":256},{"uri":"Social_skills","surface_form":"socially","offset":281},{"uri":"Critic","surface_form":"critic","offset":366}]}